    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 170, Number 56 (Tuesday, April 2, 2024)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. FITZGERALD:H.R. 7857.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8 of the United States ConstitutionThe single subject of this legislation is:This bill would codify the long-standing requirement thatFannie Mae and Freddie Mac (the Enterprises) obtain a creditreport and each credit score on a borrower from each of thethree national credit bureaus when they purchase aresidential mortgage loan (the tri-merge requirement).[Page H2135]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
